-- South Africa Deploys Naval Ship to Ivory Coast, Mail & Guardian Reports
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2011-02-04T06:18:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-04/south-africa-deploys-naval-ship-to-ivory-coast-mail-guardian-reports.html
  South Africa ’s navy has deployed the
SAS Drakensberg ship to the waters off  Ivory Coast  in case it is
needed to help evacuate the country’s citizens from the west
African nation if violence worsens, Johannesburg’s Mail &
Guardian reported, citing unidentified people working for the
South African government.  The ship may also be used as a venue for negotiations, the
newspaper said, citing the people.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  